  "title": "Sales Support",
  "description": "<p>Job responsibilities</p><ul><li><p>Receive and process customer orders accurately in the system.</p></li><li><p>Follow up on order status and ensure timely delivery.</p></li><li><p>Respond to customer inquiries via email and phone promptly.</p></li><li><p>Assist in resolving customer complaints and issues.</p></li><li><p>Maintain and update customer records and sales data.</p></li><li><p>Prepare sales reports, inventory updates, and performance analysis.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with internal teams (warehouse, logistics, finance, procurement) to ensure smooth operations.</p></li><li><p>Prepare invoices and follow up on payments with customers.</p></li><li><p>Support sales team with documentation, quotations, and administrative tasks.</p></li><li></li><li>Assist in sales and marketing activities as needed (e.g., promotions, campaigns).<br /><br /><strong>Requirements</strong></li><li><li><p>1–3 years of experience in sales support, administration, or customer service.</p></li><li><p>Good understanding of sales processes, order handling, and invoicing.</p></li><li><p>Proficient in MS Office (Excel, Word, Outlook) and ERP/sales systems.</p></li><li><p>Strong communication skills (verbal and written).</p></li><p><p>Detail-oriented with good organizational and multitasking skills<br /><br />EA License No: 95C2823</p><p>EA Personnel No: R23112241</p><p>EA Personnel Name: Jin Yee</p></p></li></ul>",
